<br>
I know that druids can snare, port/evac and give you damage shields, but that's all they can really do for a warrior over a shaman...while the shammie has nice buffs, debuffs, speed, less downtime (cannibalize), pets later on to help things along, and so on and so on and so on. Frankly, if you need need snare, port/evac and damage shields in a balanced group, I'd look for a wizard and make sure to leave a spot open in the group for a shaman.<br>
<br>
I know that when I play the warrior I'd rather have my wife's cleric or shaman with me than my own druid. I just bring the druid in at the end of the evening to port peeps out.<br>
<br>
I still love my little druid, and do continue to play him (he has 101 days /played...was my first &quot;serious&quot; EQ character, so I spent a *lot* of time with him), but I have to say that if I had to do it all over again, I'd pick a barbarian shaman in a hot second over a druid.<br>
<br>
